        <h2>What is EJS?</h2>
        <p>EJS (Embedded JavaScript) is a simple templating language that lets you generate HTML markup with plain JavaScript. It's a popular choice for server-side rendering in Node.js applications.</p>

        <h2>Key Features of EJS</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Fast compilation and rendering</li>
            <li>Simple template tags: <code>&lt;% %&gt;</code></li>
            <li>Custom delimiters (e.g., use <code>[? ?]</code> instead of <code>&lt;% %&gt;</code>)</li>
            <li>Includes</li>
            <li>Both server-side and client-side support</li>
            <li>Static caching of intermediate JavaScript</li>
            <li>Static caching of templates</li>
            <li>Complies with the Express view system</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Why Use EJS?</h2>
        <p>EJS is a great choice for developers who are comfortable with HTML and JavaScript. It allows you to use plain JavaScript to generate HTML, making it easier to create dynamic web pages without learning a new syntax.</p>

